ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes. We can learn some new methods to solve problems.
I would definitely recommend this course to the fellow students. Even though it might be difficult at times, once learned, it can be really helpful to the future studies.
Don't take 505 if Dr. Loewenberg is the instructor. Under another instructor though, I would recommend the course as a review for linear algebra and differential equations.
Yes, the math skills are trully useful.
I strongly recommend this course. Knowledge incorporated in this course is very helpful for engineers.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course has been very helpful to me since it is the fundamental knowledge to an engineer. I have learned some of the content covered in this course before as an undergraduate student, but still I felt I was learning so much more.
Felt like an undergrad engineering weed out course. Not what I would have expected from a graduate course. Did not contribute to research/deepen my knowledge of my discipline.
It would be helpful for us studying the basic course 'Transport'.
